sentences: Alexis Jordan (born April 7, 1992) is an American singer and actress from Columbia, South Carolina.
Jordan rose to fame as a contestant on the first season of America's Got Talent in 2006 at the age of 14.
Her debut single, "Happiness", was released in September 2010, and reached number one in the Netherlands and Norway, and also became a top-three hit in Australia and the United Kingdom.
Jordan's debut self-titled album was released on February 25, 2011.
"Good Girl" was released as Jordan's second single in February 2011.
Her self-titled debut album was released on February 25, 2011.
